article.headline: Richmond 59, Temple 52
article.story: PHILADELPHIA (AP) -- Mike Skrocki scored 13 of his 17 points in the second half and made four late free throws to lift Richmond to a 59-52 win over Temple Saturday night. Reggie Brown had 14 points and four 3-pointers, both season-highs, while Tony Dobbins added 10 points for the Spiders (9-8, 2-3 Atlantic 10), who ended a three-game losing skid. David Hawkins led the Owls (5-8, 1-3) with 26 points. Mardy Collins had 16 points and seven rebounds. Richmond opened the second half with a 16-4 run that erased a one-point halftime deficit and gave the Spiders a 41-30 lead. Temple shot 2-for-14 during that stretch, while the Spiders got baskets on six straight possessions. The Owls pulled within four on a 3 by Hawkins with 7:19 to play, but went scoreless for the next 4:05 before Hawkins hit a reverse layup. The lead was cut to four again with 1:33 remaining before Skrocki sank four free throws. Hawkins hit another 3, but Brown put the game out of reach with two foul shots. Owls center Keith Butler, who was suffering from bronchitis early in the week, played only seven minutes and was held scoreless. Temple was 7-for-31 on 3-pointers and shot 35.7 percent from the field. Hawkins scored 13 consecutive points and hit 3-of-7 3-point attempts in the first half.
